<P><H1 align=center>ADDRESS DETAILS – DC065</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>areas shown in red are mandatory and must be completed to 
proceed</FONT>           </P>
<P>This screen registers details about the applicant’s current, correspondence, 
previous or additional addresses. If the applicant has not been resident at the 
property for more than three years, previous address details may need to be 
taken.</P>
<P><H3>Address details: </H3>complete the postcode and address 
details in the relevant fields. If the current address is being edited, the 
fields will be populated with the address information entered previously.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Nature of Occupancy: </H3>select the relevant option 
from the drop-down list – whether the applicant is a home owner, tenant, staying 
with a relative / friend, other.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Note: </H3>if the tenant option is selected, the 
‘Tenancy’ button in the bottom right of the screen will be activated. Clicking 
on this leads to ‘<A HREF="HELP_DC066.asp">Tenancy Details</A>’ (DC066), where landlord details can be 
registered. 
<P></P>
<P><H3>What are you going to do with the property?: </H3>the 
options on this drop-down list are ‘selling’, ‘not selling’ and ‘already sold’. 
Therefore if the applicant is a home owner, this should be completed
<P></P>
<P><H3>Date moved in: </H3>this field must be completed before 
proceeding. This is to check the length of residency and take previous address 
details if necessary
<P></P>
<P><H3>Another: </H3>if previousother (E.g. previous or 
correspondence) address details are required, click on ‘Another’ to enter the 
details
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>clicking on ‘OK’ leads back to Address Summary 
(DC060) the previous screen.

